}

// scroll 

// get DOM object width:
element.scrollWidth => total content width
element.offsetWidth => visible content width + border width + scrollbar width
element.clientWidth => visible content width without boders and scrollbars
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/21064101/understanding-offsetwidth-clientwidth-scrollwidth-and-height-respectively
